Interface Ipv6

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, Ipv6Types, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Ipv6Stub

    public interface Ipv6
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, Ipv6Types, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The Ipv6 interface provides methods to perform IPv6 network configuration for interfaces. This interface was added in vSphere API 6.7.

    • Method Detail

      • set

        Ipv6.SetInvocation set(java.lang.String interfaceName,
                       Ipv6Types.Config config)
        Set IPv6 network configuration for specific interface. This method was added in vSphere API 6.7.
        Parameters:
        interfaceName - Network interface to update, for example, "nic0". The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.appliance.networking.interfaces.
        config - The IPv6 configuration.
        Returns:
        instance of Ipv6.SetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described set operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        ResourceBusy - The specified NIC is busy.
        NotFound - The specified NIC is not found.
        Error - Generic error.

      • get

        Ipv6.GetInvocation get(java.lang.String interfaceName)
        Get IPv6 network configuration for specific interface. This method was added in vSphere API 6.7.

        Invocation Result:
        IPv6 configuration.

        Parameters:
        interfaceName - Network interface to query, for example, "nic0". The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.appliance.networking.interfaces.
        Returns:
        instance of Ipv6.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if the specified NIC is not found.
        Error - Generic error.
